      "side": 1,
      "message": "I have now adjusted the string formatting so that there is always a line break before “by”. This should at least ensure that the names of the participants who are recording are visible, and that there is hardly any overlapping text anymore.\n\nAs mentioned, I would keep the entire text unchanged, i.e. in the form “This call is being recorded by %1”, and not modify it, because in my opinion it is the easiest to translate and also remains unambiguous across other languages.\n\nOnly if this is an absolute no-go would we need to consider alternative source texts that also allow for unambiguous translation into all languages. See the following link for details: https://git.jami.net/savoirfairelinux/jami-client-qt/-/work_items/2250#note_57653",
